The management of LEADERSHIP Group, yesterday paid a condolence visit to the Friday editor, Mr. Richard Abu, who lost his only wife. The editorial director, Mr. George Agba who led the management of LEADERSHIP Group, on the condolence visit on behalf of the chairman of LEADERSHIP Group, Mr Sam Nda-Isaiah, in Abuja,  expressed sadness over the death. Agba sympathised with the immediate family noting that the wife would be greatly missed by the family and all that had come in contact with her. He said that it is very sad and painful to lose the mother of a family, stressing that her demise has created a great vacuum that would be hard to fill. In his response, the husband of the deceased and editor LEADERSHIP Friday, Mr Richard Abu noted that death is the expected end of every mortal. He described his late wife as a fruitful woman, and said that the family has taken solace in the words of God which say “everything under the sun has time, a time to be born, and time to die.” Abu disclosed that his late wife passed on after a brief illness.